    <statement><p>Add or subtract the rational expressions to a single rational expression and then simplify. If applicable, state the restricted domain.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{{\frac{5}{r-5}-\frac{10r}{r^{2}-25}} =}</m> <fillin characters="40" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>-\frac{5}{r+5}, r\ne 5</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
   {\frac{5}{r-5}-\frac{10r}{r^{2}-25}} 
      \amp = {\frac{5}{r-5}}-\frac{10 r}{(r - 5)(r + 5)} \\
      \amp = \frac{5\cdot({r+5})}{({r-5})\cdot({r+5})} -\frac{10 r}{(r - 5)(r + 5)} \\
      \amp = \frac{{5\mathopen{}\left(r+5\right)-10r}}{(r - 5)(r + 5)} \\
      \amp = \frac{{5r+25-10r}}{(r - 5)(r + 5)} \\
      \amp = \frac{{-5r+25}}{(r - 5)(r + 5)} \\
      \amp = \frac{{-5\mathopen{}\left(r-5\right)}}{(r - 5)(r + 5)} \\
      \amp = {-\frac{5}{r+5}, r\ne 5}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p>Since the factor <m>{r-5}</m> was canceled, the domain condition lost during the simplification is <m>r \ne {5}</m>.</p>
</solution>
